==English==
===Contraction===
'''That'd'''

as in ''that'd be great''

# the contraction of ''that would.''

This contraction is another word that has moved into the written language from the use of the internet and instant messages for communication and humans habit of shortening commonly used phrases. It has been in frequent use in the spoken language. This word is improper english and holds the same status as "ain't" but is almost universally understood.